ce:section.ce:para:
Compared with many nanozymes with only single-enzyme mimic activity, the nanozymes with multi-enzyme mimic activity as well as other functions are rare. Based on the above, we fabricate three fluorescent nanozymes with laccase- and peroxidase-like activities under moderate conditions. Nanozyme precursors are fabricated by coordination interactions between Cu2+, Fe3+ and adenosine phosphate. Then, three fluorescent nanozymes, NH2BDC/CuFe/ATP (NPs-1), NH2BDC/CuFe/ADP (NPs-2), NH2BDC/CuFe/AMP (NPs-3), are constructed by absorbing fluorescent amino terephthalic acid (NH2-BDC) to the surface of precursors. Three nanozymes show fluorescence property (λ
                     em = 445 nm), laccase-like and peroxidase-like activities (Scheme 1
                     ). The laccase-like activity shows an upward trend with a decrease in the number of the phosphate group of the metal ligand. In comparison with HRP, NPs-1 possesses many advantages, including higher affinity with substrates, easy preparation and stability, which facilitate the utilization of peroxidase mimics in the biosensing field. Thus, a detection system to determine H2O2 and AA is established via the excellent fluorescence property and peroxidase-like activity of NPs-1. Scheme 1 reveals the principle of this detection system. NPs-1 catalyze H2O2 to produce ·OH. Subsequently, under the oxidase of ·OH with much strong oxide ability, OPD is oxidized to 2,3-diaminophenazine (DAP) which reduces the fluorescence of NPs-1 based on the inner filter effect (IFE), while the fluorescence could recover because of the oxidation of AA to produce dehydroascorbic acid (DAA). Then this system is successfully employed to determine AA in vitamin C tablets. Additionally, this work develops a smartphone-based detection of AA by measuring the intrinsic fluorescence of NPs-1.
